Load the compiled magic database from the embedded ZIP (Pattern 2).

Upstream file expects $datadir/share/misc/magic.mgc on disk (or $MAGIC, or
~/.magic.mgc). For unpins we ship a single binary: magic.mgc rides the binary's
single metadata/runtime ZIP at EOF (withRuntimeData), zstd-compressed (~340 KB
vs ~10.6 MB raw -- the db is sparse and compresses ~31x). file.c::load() pulls
it back via unpin_load_embedded_magic() (unpin_magic.c, on the unpin-vfs
self-EOF reader) and hands the buffer to magic_load_buffers when no magic file
is given on the command line and $MAGIC is unset; user-supplied -m or $MAGIC
still go through the regular magic_load path so power users can override.

This replaces the older compiled-in-blob approach (embedded_magic.h via xxd),
which baked the raw 10.6 MB db into the binary's rodata -- and, for the mega
multicall, into its bitcode module. The ZIP overlay carries it compressed and is
merged into the mega like the man pages.

